03:24.395 --> 03:25.428
He can't be gone.

03:26.397 --> 03:27.530
I should have been here.

03:29.901 --> 03:31.868
This is no time for regret.

03:31.970 --> 03:34.152
We were caught off guard,
and we paid the price.

03:34.439 --> 03:35.972
The Warlock Lord is gone.

03:36.074 --> 03:37.872
He must be on his way to Heaven's Well.

03:37.879 --> 03:39.712
We have to go after him.

03:41.546 --> 03:43.207
He died for nothing.

03:43.214 --> 03:45.481
No. He died to protect you.

03:46.217 --> 03:47.483
He was right to do so.

03:57.462 --> 03:59.495
This world owes Allanon a great debt.

04:13.451 --> 04:15.013
We're gonna do what Allanon wanted

04:15.947 --> 04:16.978
and we're gonna fight.

04:18.182 --> 04:19.281
This isn't over.

04:20.985 --> 04:23.853
We cannot let your father's
sacrifice be in vain. Understand?

04:25.123 --> 04:27.990
There's no time for fear,
no time for doubt.

04:28.092 --> 04:29.725
Everything hangs in the balance.

04:32.359 --> 04:34.127
This doesn't work without
the both of you.

04:35.199 --> 04:37.099
The Druid and the Shannara.

05:19.377 --> 05:22.044
Please, Eretria, don't do this.

05:22.747 --> 05:23.779
Untie me.

05:28.453 --> 05:29.885
I brought you the Princess.

05:40.331 --> 05:41.831
Such beauty.

06:01.219 --> 06:04.120
Heaven's Well awaits.

06:45.530 --> 06:47.263
No signs of a siege.

06:47.365 --> 06:48.964
You think we made it in time?

06:49.067 --> 06:51.534
Can't say. But one way or another,

06:52.870 --> 06:54.170
the battle ends here.

07:04.148 --> 07:07.316
I want archers on every balcony.
Cover every approach.

07:07.418 --> 07:10.086
Do we know the size or scope
of the Warlock Lord's army?

07:10.188 --> 07:12.488
My scouts report no evidence of an army.

07:12.590 --> 07:14.757
If he is marching on Leah,
he's traveling light.

07:14.859 --> 07:17.770
Oh he's marching all right.
He wants Heaven's Well.

07:17.777 --> 07:19.423
Have your men
heard anything from Allanon?

07:19.430 --> 07:20.529
Nothing yet.

07:21.586 --> 07:24.821
You have your orders, people.
Now let's batten it down.

07:25.007 --> 07:27.107
And if this is our last show,

07:27.114 --> 07:28.714
let's make sure it's a damn good one.

07:33.816 --> 07:36.984
The river must flow with my blood.

07:38.320 --> 07:39.453
Yes, my lord.

07:40.422 --> 07:41.655
Eretria, please.

07:42.497 --> 07:43.896
Don't listen to him.

07:43.903 --> 07:45.770
Okay, I know you're still in there.

07:46.893 --> 07:48.926
If we let him have his way,

07:50.129 --> 07:52.396
my people, our friends,

07:53.065 --> 07:54.073
will die.

07:55.568 --> 07:57.301
I need you to fight for us.

07:57.308 --> 07:58.607
Enough!

08:11.684 --> 08:13.417
Do as I command.

08:45.667 --> 08:47.634
The Well is inside a temple,
behind those falls.

08:47.641 --> 08:48.840
You'll have to go up on foot.

08:51.072 --> 08:53.273
Spoken like a man
who's not coming with us.

08:53.280 --> 08:55.994
I must return to the palace
to protect the dam.

08:56.411 --> 08:58.745
If the Warlock Lord poisons
Heaven's Well,

08:58.847 --> 09:00.980
and his blood gets into the reservoir,

09:01.082 --> 09:02.382
the dam will be the only thing

09:02.484 --> 09:04.884
holding back the tide of darkness.

09:04.986 --> 09:07.120
Nothing quite like a Druid pep talk.

09:09.291 --> 09:11.824
You have the sword. You have each other.

09:11.927 --> 09:14.027
You've seen your truth,
and now you must embrace it.

09:15.497 --> 09:17.363
May the shades of your fathers
watch over you.

09:18.334 --> 09:19.361
Good luck.

09:46.394 --> 09:48.361
This is where your men should be
when we come in.

09:48.580 --> 09:49.658
Eretria,

09:50.699 --> 09:51.731
where's Allanon?

09:54.035 --> 09:56.302
Give it to me straight.
How screwed are we?

09:56.404 --> 09:57.937
The Warlock Lord has Lyria.

09:58.039 --> 09:59.839
And he's heading to Heaven's Well.

09:59.941 --> 10:01.607
We must protect the dam at all costs.

10:03.645 --> 10:05.578
Is there a control room
for the spillways?

10:06.923 --> 10:07.952
Follow me.

10:31.306 --> 10:34.540
Soon my shadow will
extend across the Four Lands.

10:44.652 --> 10:45.785
What do you want from me?

11:05.507 --> 11:08.107
You are the key.

11:37.572 --> 11:38.871
You're free now.

12:18.938 --> 12:21.211
We have to assume he's
already made it to the Well.

12:21.674 --> 12:22.739
Stay alert.

12:24.243 --> 12:26.543
- Wil, wait.
- What's up?

12:26.979 --> 12:28.178
Nothing. Just,

12:29.648 --> 12:32.115
everything actually.

12:32.218 --> 12:35.232
First Allanon tells me I'm
the future of the Druid Order,

12:35.239 --> 12:37.238
and now you're saying that
I'm Queen of the Elves,

12:37.245 --> 12:40.012
and now the fate of
the Four Lands is in our hands.

12:41.060 --> 12:42.893
It's a lot to carry.

12:42.995 --> 12:44.661
Do you remember when you stalked me

12:44.763 --> 12:47.598
at the tavern in Storlock
and you told me,

12:47.700 --> 12:49.166
what was it again?

12:49.268 --> 12:50.901
To drop the tortured loner act.

12:52.004 --> 12:54.037
And I wasn't stalking you.

12:54.139 --> 12:57.007
Uh. Well, I guess it's my turn to say

12:57.109 --> 13:00.444
you're a much better badass
than you are a reluctant hero.

13:03.048 --> 13:06.666
Look, I know I was kind
of a jerk to you when we first met.

13:06.752 --> 13:08.085
Kind of?

13:08.187 --> 13:09.753
What I'm trying to say is that

13:10.789 --> 13:12.322
I get it.

13:12.424 --> 13:14.391
I get why you didn't wanna help me.

13:14.493 --> 13:16.393
Why you couldn't just get over it.

13:16.400 --> 13:18.323
It's okay. You didn't know
what I'd been through.

13:18.330 --> 13:20.030
But you warned me.

13:20.132 --> 13:22.165
You told me that magic
would only bring me pain.

13:23.202 --> 13:24.668
So did Allanon.

13:24.770 --> 13:25.836
But I didn't listen.

13:29.475 --> 13:32.242
Until you have lived with magic,

13:32.344 --> 13:33.577
you can't know its price.

13:36.282 --> 13:38.582
You should know something,
while we're clearing the air.

13:38.984 --> 13:40.045
What?

13:40.052 --> 13:43.387
When we first met, I was just looking

13:43.489 --> 13:45.589
for an excuse to wallow in my pain.

13:46.325 --> 13:48.125
And you snapped me out of it.

13:49.762 --> 13:52.763
I wouldn't be here without you.
You know that, right?

13:55.567 --> 13:57.167
Good.

13:57.269 --> 13:59.670
Because there's no one
I'd rather have by my side.

14:02.715 --> 14:04.730
Well, then I guess
we've got some climbing to do.

14:08.762 --> 14:09.908
All right

14:51.218 --> 14:53.687
_

14:54.817 --> 14:56.904
